.TH SHRUTZ 1 "2026-07-22" "shrutz" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
shrutz \- active-time wallpaper rotator for macOS
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B shrutz
.I command
.RI [ args ]
.PP
.B shrutz
.RB [ \-v | \-\-version ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B shrutz
is a wallpaper rotation daemon for macOS that only counts time you are
actively using your computer. The timer ticks only when keyboard or mouse
input has been detected within the last 60 seconds. Walk away and the
timer freezes exactly where it left off.
.PP
Wallpapers are applied across every Mission Control Space simultaneously
by writing directly into the macOS wallpaper store
.RI ( Index.plist )
and restarting the wallpaper agent.
.PP
Images are organised into named
.I sets
under
.IR ~/.local/lib/shrutz/wallpapers/ .
Only one set is active at a time. Switching sets changes the wallpaper
pool immediately without resetting the active-time counter.
.SH DAEMON COMMANDS
.TP
.B shrutz status
Show whether the launchd daemon is running, its PID, and last exit code.
Add
.B \-\-json
for machine-readable output (used by the menu bar companion app).
.TP
.B shrutz start
Load and start the launchd agent.
.TP
.B shrutz stop
Unload and stop the launchd agent.
.TP
.B shrutz log
Stream the live activity log with
.BR tail (1).
Interrupt with Ctrl-C.
.TP
.B shrutz update
Pull the latest version from the git repository recorded at install time,
re-run
.BR install.sh ,
and restart the daemon. Requires the repo to still be present on disk.
.TP
.B shrutz menubar install
Build the Swift menu bar companion app from the recorded git repository
and install it to
.IR ~/Applications .
Opt-in only \(em never invoked by
.BR install.sh .
Requires Xcode (or the Command Line Tools) to be installed.
.TP
.B shrutz menubar uninstall
Prompts
.B really?
and, on confirmation, quits the app if it's running and removes
.I ~/Applications/Shrutz.app .
If "Launch at Login" had been enabled from the app's own Preferences,
macOS may still show a stale Login Items entry afterward \(em remove it
manually from System Settings \(-> General \(-> Login Items.
.TP
.BR "shrutz \-v" ", " "shrutz \-\-version"
Print the installed version, read from
.IR ~/.local/lib/shrutz/VERSION .
Prints
.B "shrutz unknown"
if that file is missing.
.SH PLAYBACK COMMANDS
.TP
.B shrutz now
Print the current wallpaper filename, set name, position in the set,
active-time progress, and time remaining until the next switch.
Appends
.B [PAUSED]
if the timer is frozen. Add
.B \-\-json
for machine-readable output.
.TP
.B shrutz next
Advance immediately to the next wallpaper. The active-time counter is
not affected.
.TP
.B shrutz prev
Go back to the previous wallpaper. The active-time counter is
not affected.
.TP
.B shrutz pause
Freeze the active-time counter. The daemon keeps running and the
wallpaper stays put until
.B shrutz resume
is called.
.TP
.B shrutz resume
Unfreeze the active-time counter.
.TP
.B shrutz dash
Open a live terminal dashboard that refreshes every 5 seconds.
Displays the current wallpaper, timer progress bar, daemon uptime,
total switch count, and the last five history entries.
Press
.B q
to exit.
.SH SET COMMANDS
.TP
.B shrutz sets
List all wallpaper sets with image count, creation date, and a marker
indicating the active set. Add
.B \-\-json
for machine-readable output.
.TP
.BI "shrutz set create " "name " [ source-path ]
Create a new wallpaper set. If
.I source-path
is provided, images from that path are imported into the new set
immediately.
.TP
.BI "shrutz set delete " name
Delete a wallpaper set and all its images after a confirmation prompt.
The active set cannot be deleted; switch to another set first.
.TP
.BI "shrutz set rename " "old new"
Rename a wallpaper set. If the renamed set is currently active,
.B ACTIVE_SET
in the state file is updated and the daemon is restarted.
.TP
.BI "shrutz set info " name
Show detailed information about a set: creation date, image count, disk
usage. For the active set, also shows current position and timer progress.
.TP
.BI "shrutz set shuffle " "name " "on" | "off"
Enable or disable shuffle mode for a set. When enabled, the daemon
generates a random play order that covers every image before repeating.
The active-time counter is not affected when shuffle is toggled.
.TP
.BI "shrutz switch " set
Switch the active wallpaper set. The wallpaper changes immediately and
position resets to the first image of the new set. The active-time
counter is preserved.
.TP
.BI "shrutz import " path " [" --set " " name ]"
Copy supported images from
.I path
(a file or directory) into the active set. Use
.B --set
.I name
to import into a specific set without switching to it. Duplicates
(matched by filename) are skipped. Supported formats:
.BR .jpg ,
.BR .jpeg ,
.BR .png ,
.BR .heic ,
.BR .webp .
.TP
.BI "shrutz export " "set " [ destination ]
Create a
.B .zip
archive of a wallpaper set including its metadata. Destination defaults
to
.IR ~/Desktop .
.SH GALLERY COMMANDS ("Creators Publish")
shrutz ships with no bundled wallpapers. This is a small catalog of
developer-curated sets \(em including the original
.B haasan
set \(em hosted as a JSON manifest on GitHub, that any user can browse
and optionally download. Nothing here runs automatically; it's purely
opt-in.
.TP
.B shrutz gallery list
Fetch and display the available sets: name, author, image count,
whether it's already installed locally, and a short description. Add
.B \-\-json
for machine-readable output.
.TP
.BI "shrutz gallery install " name " [\-\-as " local-name ]
Download and extract a set into a new local wallpaper set directory. Use
.B \-\-as
to install it under a different local name. Verifies a checksum if the
manifest provides one. Refuses if a set with that local name already
exists. Does not change the active set \(em switch to it afterward with
.BR "shrutz switch" .
.SH WEATHER COMMANDS
Automatic wallpaper switching based on live weather conditions at a
location you set once. Uses the free, no-API-key Open-Meteo service for
both weather data and city-name geocoding \(em no signup or credentials
required.
.TP
.BR "shrutz weather" " | " "shrutz weather status"
Show whether auto-switching is enabled, the configured location, the
last-observed condition and temperature, and the full condition-to-set
mapping table. Add
.B \-\-json
for machine-readable output.
.TP
.B shrutz weather on
Enable auto-switching. Requires a location to already be set.
.TP
.B shrutz weather off
Disable auto-switching. The daemon keeps running normally; only the
weather-driven switching stops.
.TP
.BI "shrutz weather location " "city-name | lat,lon"
Set the location used for weather lookups. A bare
.I lat,lon
pair (e.g.
.IR 42.36,-71.06 )
is stored directly; anything else is resolved to coordinates via
Open-Meteo's geocoding API.
.TP
.BI "shrutz weather map " "condition set"
Map a weather condition to one of your wallpaper sets. Valid conditions:
.BR clear ,
.BR cloudy ,
.BR fog ,
.BR rain ,
.BR snow ,
.BR storm ,
.BR night .
The
.B night
mapping, if configured, only overrides
.B clear
and
.B cloudy
after dark \(em severe weather (rain/snow/storm/fog) is shown regardless
of time of day.
.TP
.BI "shrutz weather unmap " condition
Remove a condition's mapping.
.TP
.B shrutz weather check
Force an immediate weather check and switch decision, without waiting
for the next scheduled poll.
.SH INFO COMMANDS
.TP
.B shrutz stats
Show daemon uptime, total wallpaper switches, number of sets, total
image count, active set name, and current timer progress. Add
.B \-\-json
for machine-readable output.
.TP
.BI "shrutz history " [ n ]
Show the last
.I n
wallpaper switches from the activity log, formatted as a table with
timestamp, position, and filename.
.I n
defaults to 10.
.TP
.B shrutz config
Print the current tunable values. Add
.B \-\-json
for machine-readable output.
.TP
.BI "shrutz config " "key value"
Set a tunable and restart the daemon so it takes effect immediately.
Valid keys:
.RS
.TP
.B ACTIVE_MINS
Minutes of real active use before advancing to the next wallpaper.
Default: 30.
.TP
.B IDLE_THRESHOLD
Seconds without keyboard or mouse input before the user is considered
away and the timer freezes. Default: 60.
.TP
.B CHECK_EVERY
How often the daemon polls idle time and checks for mismatches, in
seconds. Default: 30.
.TP
.B WEATHER_POLL_MINS
How often the daemon polls the weather API when auto-switching is
enabled, in minutes. Default: 20.
.RE
.SH UNINSTALL COMMANDS
.TP
.B shrutz dieanddontcomeback
Remove the shrutz binary after confirmation. Prompts
.B really?
and proceeds only if the answer contains the word
.I yes
(case-insensitive).
Your wallpaper sets, state file, and logs under
.I ~/.local/lib/shrutz/
are left completely untouched. The launchd agent is stopped before
the binary is removed.
.TP
.BR "shrutz dieanddontcomeback \-\-ever" " | " "\-e"
Full uninstall after confirmation. Stops the daemon, removes the binary,
the launchd agent plist, the man page, and the entire
.I ~/.local/lib/shrutz/
tree including all wallpaper sets, state, and logs. Also strips the
.B PATH
and
.B MANPATH
lines added by the installer from
.I .zshrc
and
.IR .bashrc .
There is no undo.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.local/bin/shrutz
The main executable.
.TP
.I ~/.local/lib/shrutz/wallpapers/<set>/
Wallpaper image directories. Each set contains a
.B __init__
metadata file (name, created date, image count, optional shuffle flag).
.TP
.I ~/.local/lib/shrutz/state
Bash-sourceable key=value file persisting runtime state across reboots:
.BR CURRENT_INDEX ,
.BR ACTIVE_SECONDS ,
.BR ACTIVE_SET ,
.BR PAUSED ,
.BR PLAY_ORDER ,
.BR SHRUTZ_REPO ,
and the weather fields
.BR WEATHER_ENABLED ,
.BR WEATHER_LAT ,
.BR WEATHER_LON ,
.BR WEATHER_LOCATION_LABEL ,
.BR WEATHER_LAST_POLL ,
.BR WEATHER_LAST_SET ,
.BR WEATHER_LAST_CONDITION ,
.BR WEATHER_LAST_TEMP_F .
.TP
.I ~/.local/lib/shrutz/weather_map
Flat
.I condition=set-name
mapping file, one line per mapping, managed via
.BR "shrutz weather map/unmap" .
.TP
.I ~/.local/lib/shrutz/VERSION
The installed version string, copied from the repo's
.I VERSION
file at install time. Read by
.BR "shrutz --version" .
.TP
.I ~/.local/lib/shrutz/shrutz.log
Activity log. Written by the daemon on every significant event.
.TP
.I ~/.local/lib/shrutz/shrutz.err
Standard error output from the daemon. Useful for crash diagnosis.
.TP
.I ~/.local/etc/launchd/local.shrutz.plist
launchd agent definition. Source of truth; symlinked into
.IR ~/Library/LaunchAgents/ .
.TP
.I ~/Library/Application\ Support/com.apple.wallpaper/Store/Index.plist
macOS wallpaper store (binary plist). Written by shrutz on every
wallpaper switch to update all Mission Control Spaces simultaneously.
.TP
.I ~/Applications/Shrutz.app
The optional Swift menu bar companion app, installed by
.BR "shrutz menubar install" .
.SH SIGNALS
The daemon responds to the following signals:
.TP
.B SIGUSR1
Advance to the next wallpaper immediately (sent by
.BR "shrutz next" ).
.TP
.B SIGUSR2
Go back to the previous wallpaper (sent by
.BR "shrutz prev" ).
.TP
.B SIGHUP
Toggle pause/resume (sent by
.B shrutz pause
and
.BR "shrutz resume" ).
.TP
.B SIGTERM
Restart (sent by
.BR "shrutz switch" ,
.BR "shrutz set rename" ,
.BR "shrutz config" ,
and the
.BR "shrutz weather on/off/location/map/unmap"
commands).
Also sent by
.B shrutz dieanddontcomeback
to stop the daemon before removal.
launchd with
.B KeepAlive=true
restarts the daemon automatically on all cases except uninstall, where
the plist is unloaded first.
.SH REQUIREMENTS
macOS 14 Sonoma or later. bash and python3 (both ship with macOS).
No third-party software dependencies. The weather and gallery features
are entirely opt-in and require network access to
.I api.open-meteo.com
/
.I geocoding-api.open-meteo.com
(weather) or
.I raw.githubusercontent.com
/
.I github.com
(gallery) only when actually used; nothing is contacted otherwise.
Building the menu bar companion app additionally requires Xcode.
.SH INSTALLATION
.nf
git clone https://github.com/burpcat/shrutz.git
cd shrutz
chmod +x shrutz install.sh
\&./install.sh
.fi
.PP
On a fresh install, the installer prompts you to name your first
wallpaper set (this becomes the active set) and optionally import a
folder of images into it. Press Enter to accept the default name
.RB ( main )
or to skip the import \(em add images later with
.BR "shrutz import" .
shrutz ships with no bundled wallpapers; browse developer-curated sets,
including the original
.B haasan
set, with
.BR "shrutz gallery list" .
Re-running
.B install.sh
on an existing install (repairs, upgrades) skips this prompt entirely.
After installation reload your shell:
.PP
.nf
source ~/.zshrc
.fi
.PP
The installer adds two lines to your
.I .zshrc
or
.IR .bashrc :
.PP
.nf
export PATH="$HOME/.local/bin:$PATH"
export MANPATH="$HOME/.local/share/man:$MANPATH"
.fi
.PP
These are the only modifications made to your shell configuration.
.SH UNINSTALL
shrutz uninstalls itself. Use
.B shrutz dieanddontcomeback
to remove the binary while keeping your wallpaper sets, or
.B "shrutz dieanddontcomeback \-\-ever"
for a full wipe. Both commands prompt for confirmation before doing
anything. See
.B UNINSTALL COMMANDS
above for full details.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR launchctl (1),
.BR launchd (8),
.BR osascript (1),
.BR ioreg (8)
